WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.366
Friends,

00:00:00.366 --> 00:00:02.833
did you know that GDP can be misleading?

00:00:03.300 --> 00:00:05.000
The other day, when I was researching Iran's economy,

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:06.533
I wanted to see its GDP per capita.

00:00:06.566 --> 00:00:07.333
I saw it

00:00:07.333 --> 00:00:08.533
surged in the 1980s

00:00:08.533 --> 00:00:09.000
then declined

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:10.366
then rose again after 2000,

00:00:10.366 --> 00:00:11.100
then declined again.

00:00:11.100 --> 00:00:12.033
But do you think

00:00:12.033 --> 00:00:14.766
this is the true GDP per capita situation in Iran?

00:00:14.899 --> 00:00:17.033
I searched for "GDP per capita"

00:00:17.033 --> 00:00:18.100
and found so many options.

00:00:18.566 --> 00:00:19.633
If I clicked on this one,

00:00:19.633 --> 00:00:21.099
Iran's GDP per capita looked like this.

00:00:21.100 --> 00:00:23.633
Goodness , its peak was before the 

00:00:23.633 --> 00:00:24.533
Iranian Revolution in the 1970s

00:00:24.533 --> 00:00:25.800
and it hasn't been higher since.

00:00:25.800 --> 00:00:26.800
If I clicked on this one,

00:00:26.800 --> 00:00:27.733
it looked like this

00:00:27.733 --> 00:00:28.366
The most outrageous thing is,

00:00:28.366 --> 00:00:29.300
if I clicked on this one

00:00:30.533 --> 00:00:32.633
Iran's GDP per capita looked like this!

00:00:32.633 --> 00:00:34.533
If we analyse Iran's economy according to this chart,

00:00:34.533 --> 00:00:36.266
wouldn't everyone be Elon Musk

00:00:36.266 --> 00:00:36.733
I'm telling you,

00:00:36.733 --> 00:00:39.199
these are all statistics from the World Bank.

00:00:39.199 --> 00:00:39.866
We can't guarantee

00:00:39.866 --> 00:00:40.766
their accuracy

00:00:40.766 --> 00:00:41.966
but they're definitely official.

00:00:43.600 --> 00:00:44.199
GDP

00:00:44.199 --> 00:00:44.799
is arguably

00:00:44.800 --> 00:00:46.233
the most commonly used indicator

00:00:46.233 --> 00:00:48.033
for measuring the economy of various countries. 

00:00:48.033 --> 00:00:49.133
You might think it's just a number

00:00:49.133 --> 00:00:49.799
that won't lie

00:00:49.800 --> 00:00:51.100
but there are so many versions

00:00:51.100 --> 00:00:52.899
like the lions on the Lugou Bridge—

00:00:52.899 --> 00:00:53.566
different in

00:00:53.566 --> 00:00:54.433
sizes and shapes.

00:00:54.433 --> 00:00:55.800
The intricacies behind this are not simple.

00:00:57.500 --> 00:00:58.766
Today, let's talk about this economic indicator

00:00:58.766 --> 00:00:59.799
that you think you're most familiar with

00:00:59.800 --> 00:01:00.533
but which is actually

00:01:00.533 --> 00:01:02.399
very misleading:

00:01:02.399 --> 00:01:03.433
GDP

00:01:07.500 --> 00:01:08.000
 

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:09.933
Gross Domestic Product

00:01:09.966 --> 00:01:10.466
Gross

00:01:10.466 --> 00:01:10.999
Domestic

00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:11.533
Product

00:01:11.533 --> 00:01:12.800
as the name suggests,

00:01:12.800 --> 00:01:13.966
the total market value

00:01:13.966 --> 00:01:15.566
of all the final goods and services

00:01:15.566 --> 00:01:17.299
produced in a country or region

00:01:17.300 --> 00:01:18.033
over a certain period of time.

00:01:18.033 --> 00:01:19.000
Try to understand

00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:19.500
there are few

00:01:19.500 --> 00:01:21.000
points that are easily overlooked

00:01:21.399 --> 00:01:21.833
First,

00:01:21.833 --> 00:01:23.999
it's produced within a specific country or region.

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:25.099
For example, if a Chinese person

00:01:25.100 --> 00:01:26.699
wholly owns a Vietnamese company with all its

00:01:26.699 --> 00:01:28.133
production facilities in Vietnam

00:01:28.133 --> 00:01:29.233
whose GDP should

00:01:29.233 --> 00:01:30.600
the products be counted in?

00:01:30.766 --> 00:01:31.233
That's right,

00:01:31.233 --> 00:01:31.933
Vietnam's .

00:01:31.933 --> 00:01:33.133
Even if it's wholly owned,

00:01:33.133 --> 00:01:33.899
it's still counted in Vietnam's GDP

00:01:33.899 --> 00:01:34.833
Of course, there's another indicator

00:01:34.833 --> 00:01:35.833
called GNP 

00:01:35.833 --> 00:01:37.099
Gross National Product

00:01:37.100 --> 00:01:38.166
in which

00:01:38.166 --> 00:01:39.066
it is counted as China's GNP

00:01:39.733 --> 00:01:41.833
Second, it must be final goods.

00:01:41.899 --> 00:01:42.499
What does that mean?

00:01:42.500 --> 00:01:43.099
Let me give you an example.

00:01:43.100 --> 00:01:43.766
A chicken farm

00:01:43.766 --> 00:01:45.366
raises chickens that lay two eggs.

00:01:45.533 --> 00:01:46.366
One is sold to me

00:01:46.366 --> 00:01:47.199
and I eat it directly

00:01:47.199 --> 00:01:48.399
That's a final product

00:01:48.399 --> 00:01:49.299
because I ate it, 

00:01:49.300 --> 00:01:51.000
so it should be counted in GDP.

00:01:51.000 --> 00:01:51.833
But the other egg

00:01:51.833 --> 00:01:52.933
is sold to a restaurant and

00:01:52.933 --> 00:01:54.133
made into tomatoes scrambled eggs,

00:01:54.133 --> 00:01:54.766
then the eggs themselves

00:01:54.766 --> 00:01:56.033
shouldn't be included in GDP

00:01:56.033 --> 00:01:57.199
because they're not a final product.

00:01:57.199 --> 00:01:58.733
The scrambled eggs with tomatoes,

00:01:58.733 --> 00:02:00.100
however, should be included in GDP

00:02:00.100 --> 00:02:01.766
otherwise, there would be double counting.

00:02:01.766 --> 00:02:02.133
Of course,

00:02:02.133 --> 00:02:03.299
this isn't easy to define

00:02:03.300 --> 00:02:04.233
in real life

00:02:04.233 --> 00:02:05.300
so the accounting

00:02:05.300 --> 00:02:06.366
is prone to problems.

00:02:06.366 --> 00:02:07.600
But theoretically, that's how it should be.

00:02:08.766 --> 00:02:09.166
Furthermore

00:02:09.166 --> 00:02:10.533
not all production activities

00:02:10.533 --> 00:02:11.533
are included in GDP

00:02:11.533 --> 00:02:12.833
only transactions involving payment

00:02:12.833 --> 00:02:13.300
are counted.

00:02:13.300 --> 00:02:15.300
For example, if Wang makes a toy for his son,

00:02:15.300 --> 00:02:15.933
that doesn't count.

00:02:15.933 --> 00:02:16.699
But if Wang's son

00:02:16.699 --> 00:02:17.133
then

00:02:17.133 --> 00:02:19.166
sells that toy to Li's son next door,

00:02:19.166 --> 00:02:20.333
that's a transaction involving payment,

00:02:20.333 --> 00:02:21.499
and theoretically, it should be considered

00:02:21.500 --> 00:02:22.100
a transaction without payment.

00:02:22.100 --> 00:02:23.600
Why isn't it included in GDP?

00:02:23.600 --> 00:02:24.333
It still represents production,

00:02:24.333 --> 00:02:25.199
It has value .

00:02:25.199 --> 00:02:26.933
The problem is, it's difficult to calculate

00:02:26.933 --> 00:02:27.433
because

00:02:27.433 --> 00:02:28.833
you need a market price

00:02:28.833 --> 00:02:30.499
to measure the value of the product.

00:02:30.500 --> 00:02:32.166
Otherwise, it's just a matter of how much you say it is.

00:02:32.166 --> 00:02:32.566
For example, if

00:02:32.566 --> 00:02:34.366
I, Lin, make you a cup of

00:02:34.366 --> 00:02:35.033
secret-recipe milk tea, and

00:02:35.033 --> 00:02:35.833
you taste it and think, 

00:02:35.833 --> 00:02:36.433
Wow, it's so delicious!

00:02:36.433 --> 00:02:37.699
This milk tea is worth 1million

00:02:37.699 --> 00:02:38.366
I say that's right,

00:02:38.366 --> 00:02:39.199
it's worth 1 million.

00:02:39.199 --> 00:02:39.799
So,

00:02:39.800 --> 00:02:40.899
how much is this cup of milk tea worth?

00:02:40.899 --> 00:02:42.599
Can we include this 1 million in GDP?

00:02:42.600 --> 00:02:43.833
Obviously not, right?

00:02:43.833 --> 00:02:44.933
First, estimating

00:02:44.933 --> 00:02:46.533
such a free transaction is extremely difficult

00:02:46.533 --> 00:02:48.100
second, you don't have complete records.

00:02:48.100 --> 00:02:49.500
So, we simply don't include it in the statistics.

00:02:50.366 --> 00:02:51.199
Okay, I believe everyone

00:02:51.199 --> 00:02:52.899
has learned something by now.

00:02:52.899 --> 00:02:54.199
I'll give you a few questions to test your knowledge. 

00:02:56.566 --> 00:02:58.033
Does this count 

00:02:58.033 --> 00:02:59.300
towards GDP?

00:02:59.300 --> 00:03:01.033
I spent 500 buying a bicycle 

00:03:01.033 --> 00:03:02.133
does this count towards GDP?

00:03:02.233 --> 00:03:02.966
Yes

00:03:02.966 --> 00:03:04.066
most consumer purchases

00:03:04.066 --> 00:03:04.799
and merchandises

00:03:04.800 --> 00:03:05.566
are counted towards GDP.

00:03:05.566 --> 00:03:07.233
But if I resell this bicycle

00:03:07.233 --> 00:03:08.233
to my neighbour,

00:03:08.233 --> 00:03:09.199
does that count?

00:03:09.199 --> 00:03:09.966
No

00:03:09.966 --> 00:03:11.599
secondhand goods don't count towards GDP.

00:03:11.600 --> 00:03:12.000
So I know

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:12.800
many of you

00:03:12.800 --> 00:03:14.166
really like shopping on Xianyu (a Chinese online marketplace)

00:03:14.166 --> 00:03:15.033
practically buying everything

00:03:15.033 --> 00:03:16.199
secondhand there.

00:03:16.199 --> 00:03:17.299
Your

00:03:17.300 --> 00:03:18.466
contribution to GDP

00:03:18.466 --> 00:03:19.333
needs improvement

00:03:19.366 --> 00:03:20.533
Okay, let's go back to the bicycle

00:03:20.533 --> 00:03:22.766
let's say I add some nice stickers and modifications

00:03:22.766 --> 00:03:23.733
to this bicycle

00:03:23.733 --> 00:03:25.033
and resell it to my neighbour

00:03:25.033 --> 00:03:25.899
for 5,000 dollars.

00:03:25.899 --> 00:03:26.833
Does that count?

00:03:26.933 --> 00:03:28.033
Because I've

00:03:28.033 --> 00:03:29.433
done some extra processing

00:03:29.433 --> 00:03:30.500
and production,

00:03:30.500 --> 00:03:32.233
the added value

00:03:32.233 --> 00:03:33.433
should be counted towards GDP.

00:03:33.433 --> 00:03:35.766
But it's not actually that easy to define. 

00:03:35.800 --> 00:03:36.633
We are done about bicycles.

00:03:36.633 --> 00:03:39.199
Now, if I buy an imported sweater made overseas,

00:03:39.199 --> 00:03:40.299
does that count?

00:03:40.433 --> 00:03:42.133
The production of sweaters doesn't count,

00:03:42.133 --> 00:03:44.499
but some of that might involve domestic shipping and

00:03:44.500 --> 00:03:45.600
platform services.

00:03:45.600 --> 00:03:46.400
So this part does count.

00:03:46.500 --> 00:03:46.899
Alright, next

00:03:46.899 --> 00:03:48.133
Does buying stocks count?

00:03:48.333 --> 00:03:49.033
No.

00:03:49.033 --> 00:03:50.399
If I buy stocks at $50

00:03:50.399 --> 00:03:51.233
and they rise to $150

00:03:51.233 --> 00:03:52.600
does the $100 profit count?

00:03:52.833 --> 00:03:53.966
No, it doesn't.

00:03:53.966 --> 00:03:56.099
Stock trading is an equity transfer

00:03:56.100 --> 00:03:57.166
it's unrelated to production.

00:03:57.166 --> 00:03:58.199
So, regardless of how much you gain

00:03:58.199 --> 00:03:58.833
or lose,

00:03:58.833 --> 00:03:59.433
it doesn't count.

00:03:59.433 --> 00:04:00.033
Similarly,

00:04:00.033 --> 00:04:01.199
the increase in asset price from

00:04:01.199 --> 00:04:02.499
any investment

00:04:02.500 --> 00:04:04.300
isn't included in GDP.

00:04:04.300 --> 00:04:05.566
Therefore, a surge in stock prices

00:04:05.566 --> 00:04:07.533
doesn't directly affect GDP.

00:04:07.533 --> 00:04:08.533
What we generally call an impact

00:04:08.533 --> 00:04:09.566
is indirect,

00:04:09.566 --> 00:04:10.799
the so-called "wealth effect."

00:04:10.800 --> 00:04:11.500
When stocks rise,

00:04:11.500 --> 00:04:13.100
everyone feels richer,

00:04:13.100 --> 00:04:15.000
businesses feel stronger,

00:04:15.000 --> 00:04:15.800
and it's easier to get loans.

00:04:15.800 --> 00:04:18.566
Everyone is more inclined to invest in production

00:04:18.566 --> 00:04:20.499
which actually boosts GDP.

00:04:20.500 --> 00:04:21.333
But the stock price

00:04:21.333 --> 00:04:22.466
fluctuations themselves don't count.

00:04:22.466 --> 00:04:24.899
So, while you see many venture capital and hedge fund bigwigs

00:04:24.899 --> 00:04:26.781
making billions

00:04:26.800 --> 00:04:27.966
in the secondary market,

00:04:27.966 --> 00:04:29.733
they actually

00:04:29.733 --> 00:04:30.600
don't contribute much to GDP.

00:04:30.600 --> 00:04:32.233
However, the services provided by intermediary platforms

00:04:32.233 --> 00:04:34.066
in these transactions

00:04:34.066 --> 00:04:34.599
are counted.

00:04:34.600 --> 00:04:35.699
For example, stockbrokers

00:04:35.699 --> 00:04:36.799
charge you commissions, and

00:04:36.800 --> 00:04:38.033
investment banks earn service fees for

00:04:38.033 --> 00:04:39.100
helping companies go public

00:04:39.100 --> 00:04:39.699
These do count.

00:04:39.699 --> 00:04:40.566
Let's continue. 

00:04:40.566 --> 00:04:41.399
Does buying a house 

00:04:41.399 --> 00:04:41.999
count?

00:04:42.733 --> 00:04:43.333
New houses, yes, but

00:04:43.333 --> 00:04:44.366
secondhand houses don't.

00:04:44.366 --> 00:04:46.233
New houses are houses that have just been built

00:04:46.233 --> 00:04:47.699
and produced by developers. 

00:04:47.699 --> 00:04:48.233
If you buy one,

00:04:48.233 --> 00:04:49.533
it's considered "residential investment,"

00:04:49.533 --> 00:04:50.733
and it's included in GDP.

00:04:50.733 --> 00:04:51.399
Secondhand houses, on the other hand, 

00:04:51.399 --> 00:04:53.833
represent a transfer of ownership

00:04:53.833 --> 00:04:55.199
somewhat like a transfer of equity.

00:04:55.199 --> 00:04:56.599
So, regardless of whether the price goes up or down,

00:04:56.600 --> 00:04:57.133
it's not counted

00:04:57.133 --> 00:04:59.366
If you give this house a major renovation

00:04:59.366 --> 00:05:00.833
and suddenly increase its value, 

00:05:00.833 --> 00:05:01.799
the increase value part does count.

00:05:02.300 --> 00:05:04.033
A restaurant makes a plate of scrambled eggs with tomatoes,

00:05:04.033 --> 00:05:04.466
This does count

00:05:04.466 --> 00:05:06.333
If they make it but don't sell it,

00:05:06.333 --> 00:05:08.133
and keep it in inventory to sell later,

00:05:08.133 --> 00:05:09.366
does that count?

00:05:09.366 --> 00:05:10.500
Although it's unethical

00:05:10.500 --> 00:05:11.133
but, yes.

00:05:11.133 --> 00:05:11.766
Theoretically

00:05:11.766 --> 00:05:13.299
once a product is produced,

00:05:13.300 --> 00:05:14.899
even if it's kept in inventory and doesn't sell,

00:05:14.899 --> 00:05:15.633
it still counts.

00:05:15.633 --> 00:05:17.999
What if Wang buys a bottle of medicine or something

00:05:18.000 --> 00:05:18.966
on the black market

00:05:18.966 --> 00:05:19.566
Does it count?

00:05:19.566 --> 00:05:20.999
Theoretically, it should,

00:05:21.000 --> 00:05:21.799
but in practice, it's difficult

00:05:21.800 --> 00:05:22.733
to include in statistics.

00:05:22.733 --> 00:05:24.100
The IMF has previously calculated that

00:05:24.100 --> 00:05:25.733
the informal sector accounts for about

00:05:25.733 --> 00:05:26.766
one-third of

00:05:26.766 --> 00:05:28.199
economic activity in low- and middle-income countries.

00:05:28.199 --> 00:05:29.999
Of course, this doesn't necessarily have to be drugs or

00:05:30.000 --> 00:05:30.799
money laundering

00:05:30.800 --> 00:05:32.699
We made a cash transaction,

00:05:32.699 --> 00:05:33.699
and it's difficult to include

00:05:33.699 --> 00:05:34.333
this category in statistic

00:05:34.333 --> 00:05:35.766
Even in developed economies,

00:05:35.766 --> 00:05:37.099
this category accounts for about 15%.

00:05:37.100 --> 00:05:37.600
So, these

00:05:37.600 --> 00:05:38.833
can generally only be estimated.

00:05:38.833 --> 00:05:40.099
Get the idea? 

00:05:40.100 --> 00:05:40.899
Let's stop with the practice questions

00:05:40.899 --> 00:05:41.899
We don't have that many for you.

00:05:41.899 --> 00:05:43.233
Since GDP is

00:05:43.233 --> 00:05:44.033
Gross Domestic Product

00:05:44.033 --> 00:05:45.033
if someone tells you that

00:05:45.033 --> 00:05:47.233
GDP is the sum of everyone's income,

00:05:47.266 --> 00:05:48.499
is that wrong?

00:05:48.800 --> 00:05:49.966
Not at all.

00:05:50.033 --> 00:05:50.899
Actually, a country's

00:05:50.899 --> 00:05:52.199
total factor income

00:05:52.199 --> 00:05:53.899
equals its GDP

00:05:53.899 --> 00:05:55.766
Theoretically, they are completely equivalent.

00:05:55.766 --> 00:05:56.633
However, this income

00:05:56.633 --> 00:05:58.599
includes not only wages and salaries

00:05:58.600 --> 00:05:59.933
but also corporate profits

00:05:59.933 --> 00:06:01.166
and other miscellaneous items.

00:06:01.166 --> 00:06:02.000
Broadly speaking,

00:06:02.000 --> 00:06:04.533
GDP can be understood as the income of the entire country.

00:06:04.533 --> 00:06:06.733
So, if you look at a country's per capita income,

00:06:06.733 --> 00:06:07.733
it's different

00:06:07.733 --> 00:06:08.600
from per capita GDP.

00:06:08.600 --> 00:06:09.199
Per capita income

00:06:09.199 --> 00:06:11.399
only includes the average income of individuals,

00:06:11.399 --> 00:06:13.299
so it is generally lower than GDP per capita.

00:06:13.300 --> 00:06:14.566
For example, in 2024,

00:06:14.566 --> 00:06:16.999
the US GDP per capita was $85,800,

00:06:17.000 --> 00:06:19.100
while per capita income was $73,200.

00:06:19.100 --> 00:06:20.100
These two cannot be used interchangeably. 

00:06:20.100 --> 00:06:21.400
Here's a little tidbit for you : 

00:06:22.699 --> 00:06:23.566
In short, the value of

00:06:23.566 --> 00:06:24.966
all production value in a country,

00:06:24.966 --> 00:06:26.433
all its income

00:06:26.433 --> 00:06:27.966
and all its expenditures

00:06:27.966 --> 00:06:29.766
should theoretically be the same

00:06:29.766 --> 00:06:31.766
— all of them constitute the country's GDP.

00:06:31.766 --> 00:06:32.999
This is actually the classic

00:06:33.000 --> 00:06:34.600
three methods of calculating GDP:

00:06:34.600 --> 00:06:35.366
the production approach,

00:06:35.366 --> 00:06:36.133
the income approach

00:06:36.133 --> 00:06:37.199
and the expenditure approach

00:06:37.199 --> 00:06:38.699
It's like being in a class isn't it when someone

00:06:38.699 --> 00:06:40.699
says, "This problem has three solutions."

00:06:40.699 --> 00:06:42.133
This isn't to say that top students are particularly brilliant

00:06:42.133 --> 00:06:43.333
and want to show off their multiple solutions;

00:06:43.333 --> 00:06:44.199
it's just that GDP

00:06:44.199 --> 00:06:45.433
is very difficult to calculate.

00:06:45.433 --> 00:06:46.600
Therefore, most countries

00:06:46.600 --> 00:06:47.899
use these three methods

00:06:47.899 --> 00:06:49.633
or two of these methods

00:06:49.633 --> 00:06:50.633
cross-calculated,

00:06:50.633 --> 00:06:52.599
to ensure the accuracy of GDP.

00:06:52.600 --> 00:06:54.033
So, let's look at each of these methods one by one. 

00:06:54.033 --> 00:06:54.699
These methods

00:06:54.699 --> 00:06:55.366
might be a bit theoretical

00:06:55.366 --> 00:06:56.433
but after listening, 

00:06:56.433 --> 00:06:58.833
you'll have a deeper understanding of GDP.

00:06:59.133 --> 00:07:00.333
Let's start

00:07:00.833 --> 00:07:02.799
with the first method: the production method.

00:07:02.800 --> 00:07:04.233
GDP is the gross domestic product,

00:07:04.233 --> 00:07:05.800
so this method is the most intuitive.

00:07:05.800 --> 00:07:06.833
It sums up

00:07:06.833 --> 00:07:08.633
everyone's contribution towards the value of

00:07:08.633 --> 00:07:09.100
this product

00:07:09.100 --> 00:07:10.899
For example, a plate of scrambled egg tomatoes

00:07:10.899 --> 00:07:11.566
The restaurant

00:07:11.566 --> 00:07:12.899
buys tomatoes and eggs 

00:07:12.899 --> 00:07:13.899
for $1 each,

00:07:13.899 --> 00:07:15.233
the dish sells for $10 yuan.

00:07:15.233 --> 00:07:17.433
The extra $8

00:07:17.433 --> 00:07:18.833
is the restaurant's contribution to GDP.

00:07:18.833 --> 00:07:20.133
The tomato

00:07:20.133 --> 00:07:21.833
and egg factories also contribute.

00:07:21.833 --> 00:07:23.299
Adding up their respective added-value contributions

00:07:23.300 --> 00:07:24.000
totals $10 

00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:25.766
 is included in GDP.

00:07:25.899 --> 00:07:27.133
This way, the total added-value of

00:07:27.133 --> 00:07:28.999
every enterprise nationwide

00:07:29.000 --> 00:07:30.799
is summed to obtain the Gross Domestic Product (GDP).

00:07:30.833 --> 00:07:31.633
Its main advantage is 

00:07:31.633 --> 00:07:33.366
timeliness;

00:07:33.366 --> 00:07:34.600
the data is readily available

00:07:34.600 --> 00:07:35.733
because the entire process

00:07:35.733 --> 00:07:36.866
doesn't involve consumers

00:07:36.866 --> 00:07:37.633
and each enterprise has

00:07:37.633 --> 00:07:38.566
a clear division of labour

00:07:38.566 --> 00:07:39.599
so everyone can calculate

00:07:39.600 --> 00:07:40.699
their own added-value.

00:07:40.699 --> 00:07:42.566
Often, this method is mainly used

00:07:42.566 --> 00:07:43.599
when estimating quarterly figures

00:07:43.600 --> 00:07:44.399
but its drawbacks are

00:07:44.399 --> 00:07:45.199
also obvious

00:07:45.199 --> 00:07:46.233
it's extremely fragmented.

00:07:46.233 --> 00:07:47.800
Imagine having to

00:07:47.800 --> 00:07:48.766
isolate every single aspect

00:07:48.766 --> 00:07:50.199
of the entire economy's production process

00:07:50.199 --> 00:07:51.099
and add them all up.

00:07:51.100 --> 00:07:52.833
Even a simple dish of scrambled eggs with tomatoes

00:07:52.833 --> 00:07:54.299
has to be broken down into

00:07:54.300 --> 00:07:55.133
the restaurant portion,

00:07:55.133 --> 00:07:55.899
the egg portion,

00:07:55.899 --> 00:07:56.833
the tomato portion

00:07:56.833 --> 00:07:57.666
and then further subdividing

00:07:57.666 --> 00:07:58.500
the egg portion into

00:07:58.500 --> 00:07:59.566
the chicken farm portion and

00:07:59.566 --> 00:08:00.366
the transportation portion.

00:08:00.366 --> 00:08:01.366
In short, it 's fragmented beyond recognition

00:08:01.366 --> 00:08:02.733
It's also easy to miss

00:08:02.733 --> 00:08:03.733
or double-count.

00:08:03.733 --> 00:08:04.399
Do you know what kind of countries

00:08:04.399 --> 00:08:05.966
or regions this method

00:08:05.966 --> 00:08:06.766
is generally suitable for?

00:08:06.800 --> 00:08:09.466
Places where value-added tax is the main form of taxation,

00:08:09.466 --> 00:08:10.566
such as mainland China

00:08:10.566 --> 00:08:11.799
and many European countries.

00:08:11.800 --> 00:08:13.033
Think about the calculation of this GDP... 

00:08:13.033 --> 00:08:14.600
One of the main data sources 

00:08:14.600 --> 00:08:15.933
is tax and financial data

00:08:15.933 --> 00:08:16.899
meanwhile this value-added tax

00:08:16.899 --> 00:08:18.733
is levied on the added value,

00:08:18.733 --> 00:08:21.133
so it is naturally very compatible with the production method.

00:08:21.666 --> 00:08:23.533
The second method is the income approach

00:08:23.533 --> 00:08:25.099
which basically adds up all

00:08:25.100 --> 00:08:26.266
the income, surplus, and profits 

00:08:26.266 --> 00:08:27.633
of all companies and individuals

00:08:27.633 --> 00:08:28.966
You don't need to understand the formula; 

00:08:28.966 --> 00:08:29.333
it's not important

00:08:29.333 --> 00:08:30.333
Let's take the previous example

00:08:30.333 --> 00:08:32.233
The restaurant earned $8 right?

00:08:32.233 --> 00:08:34.166
Let's say the owner gives the chef $3 

00:08:34.166 --> 00:08:35.166
and keeps $5 for himself.

00:08:35.166 --> 00:08:36.199
How do we calculate GDP?

00:08:36.200 --> 00:08:38.000
It's $1 from eggs,

00:08:38.000 --> 00:08:39.399
$1 from tomatoes,

00:08:39.399 --> 00:08:40.666
$3 from the chef,

00:08:40.666 --> 00:08:41.733
$5 from the owner,

00:08:41.733 --> 00:08:42.700
adding up to $10

00:08:42.700 --> 00:08:43.399
That's roughly how it works

00:08:43.399 --> 00:08:44.799
The result measured by this method

00:08:44.799 --> 00:08:46.133
will generally be lower

00:08:46.133 --> 00:08:47.199
Do you know why ?

00:08:47.200 --> 00:08:48.133
Income statistics

00:08:48.133 --> 00:08:49.599
are mainly based on tax data

00:08:49.600 --> 00:08:50.600
but for the income

00:08:50.600 --> 00:08:51.700
if you report your income, you have to pay taxes.

00:08:51.700 --> 00:08:52.200
So many people

00:08:52.200 --> 00:08:53.166
might avoid reporting

00:08:53.166 --> 00:08:54.166
their income if possible

00:08:54.166 --> 00:08:55.566
such as grey income,

00:08:55.566 --> 00:08:56.399
cash income , or

00:08:56.399 --> 00:08:57.533
ambiguous income

00:08:57.533 --> 00:08:59.199
these can't be included in the statistics.

00:08:59.200 --> 00:09:00.733
Therefore, at the macro level,

00:09:00.733 --> 00:09:02.433
the overall figure

00:09:02.433 --> 00:09:03.299
is usually underestimated .

00:09:03.299 --> 00:09:04.033
That's why many countries,

00:09:04.033 --> 00:09:04.733
like China

00:09:04.733 --> 00:09:07.000
don't use this method to calculate GDP.

00:09:07.700 --> 00:09:08.799
Okay, the third approach,

00:09:08.799 --> 00:09:10.833
and the most common and important one

00:09:10.833 --> 00:09:11.899
is the expenditure approach

00:09:11.899 --> 00:09:12.899
As the name suggests,

00:09:12.899 --> 00:09:13.899
it sums up everyone's

00:09:13.899 --> 00:09:15.899
expenditure on the final goods 

00:09:15.899 --> 00:09:16.666
purchased.

00:09:16.666 --> 00:09:18.366
In the example of scrambled eggs with tomatoes

00:09:18.366 --> 00:09:20.700
Regardless of what happened during the production process 

00:09:20.700 --> 00:09:21.399
chef, boss

00:09:21.399 --> 00:09:23.299
ignore everything that happen in between

00:09:23.299 --> 00:09:25.199
as the final consumer , 

00:09:25.200 --> 00:09:26.333
I paid $10 for this final product

00:09:26.333 --> 00:09:27.899
scrambled eggs with tomatoes

00:09:27.899 --> 00:09:29.499
So, my expenditure of $10

00:09:29.500 --> 00:09:30.299
is counted in the GDP

00:09:30.399 --> 00:09:32.366
This is a simpler and more accurate

00:09:32.366 --> 00:09:33.733
method in actual measurement.

00:09:33.733 --> 00:09:35.600
Also, since people can get tax deductions

00:09:35.600 --> 00:09:37.100
when filing taxes,

00:09:37.100 --> 00:09:39.399
there's an incentive to report all expenditures.

00:09:39.399 --> 00:09:40.366
At the macro level,

00:09:40.366 --> 00:09:42.000
the statistics are more comprehensive

00:09:42.000 --> 00:09:43.000
making this expenditure method

00:09:43.000 --> 00:09:45.033
the most widely used calculation method,

00:09:45.033 --> 00:09:45.933
used by most countries.

00:09:45.933 --> 00:09:47.833
And it has a very important formula:

00:09:48.533 --> 00:09:50.933
GDP equals consumption plus investment

00:09:50.933 --> 00:09:52.766
plus government purchases plus imports and exports

00:09:52.766 --> 00:09:53.966
This formula is very important;

00:09:53.966 --> 00:09:54.799
you can memorise it

00:09:54.799 --> 00:09:55.899
or at least be familiar with it, 

00:09:55.899 --> 00:09:56.499
as it's quite commonly used.

00:09:56.500 --> 00:09:58.033
For example, many economic analyses

00:09:58.033 --> 00:09:59.833
are based on this formula,

00:09:59.833 --> 00:10:01.966
explaining why a country's GDP increased

00:10:01.966 --> 00:10:03.233
because of its consumption,

00:10:03.233 --> 00:10:04.100
investment, and

00:10:04.100 --> 00:10:05.533
government-driven growth.

00:10:05.533 --> 00:10:07.933
I won't delve into the specifics of the formula,

00:10:07.933 --> 00:10:08.933
nor do I want to be too academic,

00:10:08.933 --> 00:10:09.533
but

00:10:09.533 --> 00:10:11.599
I think it's necessary to clarify one point

00:10:11.600 --> 00:10:13.500
the investment mentioned here

00:10:13.500 --> 00:10:15.700
is different from

00:10:15.700 --> 00:10:16.600
the investment we understand in everyday life.

00:10:16.600 --> 00:10:17.733
The investment we usually talk about—

00:10:17.733 --> 00:10:18.533
buying stocks

00:10:18.533 --> 00:10:19.499
gold

00:10:19.500 --> 00:10:20.166
or funds—

00:10:20.166 --> 00:10:22.499
is not considered investment in GDP.

00:10:22.500 --> 00:10:23.566
GDP refers to

00:10:23.566 --> 00:10:25.700
the inputs of a typical enterprise for production.

00:10:25.700 --> 00:10:27.100
For example, if I bought a factory

00:10:27.100 --> 00:10:27.966
or a machine

00:10:27.966 --> 00:10:28.966
that's called an investment.

00:10:28.966 --> 00:10:30.200
So if someone tells you

00:10:30.200 --> 00:10:32.200
one day that a large influx of funds into the stock market

00:10:32.200 --> 00:10:33.500
has caused GDP to rise

00:10:33.500 --> 00:10:35.200
you can roll your eyes

00:10:36.166 --> 00:10:37.566
Speaking of which,

00:10:37.566 --> 00:10:38.533
some of you are probably wondering

00:10:38.533 --> 00:10:39.166
why we haven't explained

00:10:39.166 --> 00:10:41.033
why those GDP per capita trends in Iran

00:10:41.033 --> 00:10:41.833
are different.

00:10:41.833 --> 00:10:43.166
Well, that brings us to

00:10:43.766 --> 00:10:44.966
the various methods we just discussed

00:10:44.966 --> 00:10:46.600
how to measure GDP each year.

00:10:46.600 --> 00:10:48.133
To know GDP

00:10:48.133 --> 00:10:50.033
you can't just get a static number

00:10:50.033 --> 00:10:50.833
because it needs to be compared

00:10:50.833 --> 00:10:52.633
horizontally with different countries and

00:10:52.633 --> 00:10:54.999
vertically with different time periods.

00:10:55.000 --> 00:10:56.833
This requires different adjustments

00:10:56.833 --> 00:10:58.000
to the annual GDP data.

00:10:58.000 --> 00:10:59.366
The problem lies here:

00:10:59.366 --> 00:11:00.200
different adjustments

00:11:00.200 --> 00:11:02.500
result in drastically different GDP trend charts.

00:11:03.533 --> 00:11:04.566
The Iranian example we just mentioned

00:11:04.566 --> 00:11:05.566
is definitely not uncommon

00:11:05.566 --> 00:11:07.100
especially in developing countries.

00:11:07.100 --> 00:11:08.133
Using different adjustment methods,

00:11:08.133 --> 00:11:09.299
the resulting GDP trend charts

00:11:09.299 --> 00:11:10.433
can be completely different.

00:11:10.433 --> 00:11:11.299
Let's take it step by step.

00:11:11.299 --> 00:11:11.933
For example,

00:11:11.933 --> 00:11:14.233
if I take the annual GDP data for Iran

00:11:14.233 --> 00:11:15.200
without any processing

00:11:15.200 --> 00:11:16.666
2024 was 2.16 billion rials,

00:11:16.666 --> 00:11:18.099
2023 was 1.58 billion 

00:11:18.100 --> 00:11:19.633
plot these annual data together

00:11:19.633 --> 00:11:20.566
in a table,

00:11:20.566 --> 00:11:21.433
it looks like this.

00:11:21.600 --> 00:11:22.899
This is obviously unreasonable, right?

00:11:22.899 --> 00:11:23.899
Where does the problem lies in?

00:11:23.899 --> 00:11:25.199
It's inflation

00:11:25.200 --> 00:11:25.799
If I want to see

00:11:25.799 --> 00:11:27.599
a country's true growth,

00:11:27.600 --> 00:11:28.566
I need to adjust prices

00:11:28.566 --> 00:11:31.033
to get a figure like this: if I use last year's price level,

00:11:31.100 --> 00:11:32.600
what should this year's GDP be?

00:11:32.600 --> 00:11:33.666
This adjustment index

00:11:33.666 --> 00:11:35.199
is called the GDP deflator.

00:11:35.200 --> 00:11:36.899
It's actually similar to the inflation rate

00:11:36.899 --> 00:11:37.899
except that inflation

00:11:37.899 --> 00:11:38.966
measures the price changes 

00:11:38.966 --> 00:11:40.733
of a basket of consumer goods

00:11:40.733 --> 00:11:42.166
while the GDP deflator

00:11:42.166 --> 00:11:42.733
measures

00:11:42.733 --> 00:11:44.833
the average price changes of the entire economy.

00:11:44.833 --> 00:11:46.533
After annual price adjustments,

00:11:46.533 --> 00:11:47.833
we get the second chart:

00:11:47.833 --> 00:11:49.033
Iran's GDP per capita at

00:11:49.033 --> 00:11:49.833
constant prices

00:11:49.833 --> 00:11:50.966
calculated locally.

00:11:52.233 --> 00:11:52.633
However,

00:11:52.633 --> 00:11:53.533
this is calculated

00:11:53.533 --> 00:11:54.566
in the Iranian rial

00:11:54.566 --> 00:11:56.566
If we want to compare different countries,

00:11:56.566 --> 00:11:57.366
the most common way

00:11:57.366 --> 00:11:58.500
is to convert everything to US dollars.

00:11:58.500 --> 00:12:00.500
So, if I convert Iran's annual GDP

00:12:00.500 --> 00:12:02.533
into US dollars using the exchange rate of that year,

00:12:02.533 --> 00:12:03.766
we get the third chart:

00:12:03.766 --> 00:12:05.966
GDP per capita in current US dollars.

00:12:06.766 --> 00:12:08.899
This allows Iran to be compared horizontally with other countries.

00:12:10.100 --> 00:12:10.700
However, this chart

00:12:10.700 --> 00:12:12.600
actually includes the inflation rate of the US dollar itself,

00:12:12.600 --> 00:12:13.966
so after removing the inflation rate of the US dollar, we

00:12:13.966 --> 00:12:15.000
get the fourth chart:

00:12:15.000 --> 00:12:16.733
GDP per capita in constant US dollars.

00:12:18.566 --> 00:12:20.299
This unifies the exchange rates of various countries

00:12:20.299 --> 00:12:21.833
allowing for horizontal comparisons between countries,

00:12:21.833 --> 00:12:24.233
and also unifies the comparisons between different time periods. 

00:12:24.233 --> 00:12:25.133
This is already quite good, right?

00:12:25.133 --> 00:12:26.899
But that's not all. I have another issue to tell you.

00:12:26.899 --> 00:12:29.199
Even at the same time,

00:12:29.200 --> 00:12:30.399
the price of the same product in the US

00:12:30.399 --> 00:12:31.766
is different from its price in

00:12:31.766 --> 00:12:32.766
Iran when converted to

00:12:32.766 --> 00:12:33.533
Iranian rials.

00:12:33.533 --> 00:12:34.366
Generally, it's

00:12:34.366 --> 00:12:35.733
cheaper in developing countries,

00:12:35.733 --> 00:12:37.000
Everyone should have

00:12:37.000 --> 00:12:38.099
noticed this.

00:12:38.100 --> 00:12:39.333
I don't know if you've seen similar questions

00:12:39.333 --> 00:12:40.533
on Xiaohongshu (a Chinese social media platform)

00:12:40.533 --> 00:12:42.433
What is the equivalent of

00:12:42.433 --> 00:12:44.033
an annual income of $200,000 in New York in China?

00:12:44.100 --> 00:12:45.266
Think about it, $200,000

00:12:45.266 --> 00:12:47.133
is roughly equivalent to 1.4 million RMB.

00:12:47.133 --> 00:12:48.366
This question is actually very broad;

00:12:48.366 --> 00:12:49.933
you can think about it or argue it

00:12:49.933 --> 00:12:50.599
from countless angles.

00:12:50.600 --> 00:12:51.733
So you see the replies below

00:12:51.733 --> 00:12:52.233
are all over the place.

00:12:52.233 --> 00:12:54.100
Some say it's roughly equivalent to 300,000 RMB,

00:12:54.100 --> 00:12:54.933
some say 500,000

00:12:54.933 --> 00:12:56.099
some say 800,000

00:12:56.100 --> 00:12:58.399
In short, no one says it exceeds 1.4 million RMB.

00:12:58.399 --> 00:13:00.133
In fact, everyone agrees on the fact

00:13:00.133 --> 00:13:02.233
that the purchasing power of $200,000 in the US

00:13:02.233 --> 00:13:03.533
is definitely less than

00:13:03.533 --> 00:13:05.566
the purchasing power of 1.4 million RMB in China.

00:13:05.566 --> 00:13:06.233
Don't argue,

00:13:06.233 --> 00:13:08.200
I'm just giving a rough average purchasing power

00:13:08.200 --> 00:13:09.799
So if you want to compare

00:13:09.799 --> 00:13:11.166
the productivity of

00:13:11.166 --> 00:13:12.599
products and services produced by different countries

00:13:12.600 --> 00:13:14.333
and remove the price differences between countries,

00:13:14.333 --> 00:13:15.166
you need to use

00:13:15.166 --> 00:13:16.833
Purchasing Power Parity per capita GDP

00:13:16.833 --> 00:13:18.299
Purchasing Power Parity

00:13:18.299 --> 00:13:19.233
PPP.

00:13:19.233 --> 00:13:20.633
For example, China in 2024

00:13:20.633 --> 00:13:22.366
GDP is $18.7 trillion,

00:13:22.366 --> 00:13:23.966
so if we calculate it using purchasing power parity,

00:13:23.966 --> 00:13:25.933
it's $38.2 trillion

00:13:25.933 --> 00:13:26.999
more than double!

00:13:27.000 --> 00:13:27.766
This isn't my estimate;

00:13:27.766 --> 00:13:28.733
it 's the World Bank's estimate

00:13:28.733 --> 00:13:30.166
It actually exceeds the US's

00:13:30.166 --> 00:13:31.366
$29.2 trillion.

00:13:31.366 --> 00:13:32.933
This broadly means that,

00:13:32.933 --> 00:13:34.133
according to the World Bank's estimates,

00:13:34.133 --> 00:13:34.899
the price of the same thing

00:13:34.899 --> 00:13:35.899
in the US is 

00:13:35.899 --> 00:13:37.733
2.04 times that in China.

00:13:37.733 --> 00:13:39.566
Returning to our initial question about Xiaohongshu, a

00:13:39.566 --> 00:13:40.766
New York income of $200,000 ,

00:13:40.766 --> 00:13:41.566
calculated using PPP

00:13:41.566 --> 00:13:44.233
is equivalent to a mainland income of $98,000

00:13:44.233 --> 00:13:45.899
or 700,000 RMB

00:13:45.899 --> 00:13:47.399
You can answer that on Xiaohongshu.

00:13:47.399 --> 00:13:48.799
Just say it's a World Bank estimate.

00:13:50.100 --> 00:13:51.033
Okay, let's get back to the point.

00:13:51.033 --> 00:13:51.366
So, if

00:13:51.366 --> 00:13:52.200
you want to see the changes in Iran's

00:13:52.200 --> 00:13:53.899
real per capita productivity,

00:13:53.899 --> 00:13:55.299
you'll see this fifth chart :

00:13:55.299 --> 00:13:56.899
PPP GDP per capita

00:13:57.200 --> 00:13:58.433
But this hasn't adjusted for inflation yet

00:13:58.433 --> 00:13:59.099
After adjustment

00:13:59.100 --> 00:13:59.899
you'll see the sixth chart : 

00:13:59.899 --> 00:14:02.699
PPP GDP per capita with constant prices.

00:14:04.133 --> 00:14:04.999
I might be explaining this a bit fast,

00:14:05.000 --> 00:14:06.233
so you might be confused after listening

00:14:06.233 --> 00:14:07.000
But that's okay.

00:14:07.000 --> 00:14:08.233
In short, these six indicators

00:14:08.233 --> 00:14:09.000
assess Iran's GDP per capita based on

00:14:09.000 --> 00:14:10.133
whether the exchange rate is unified,

00:14:10.133 --> 00:14:11.233
whether purchasing power is unified,

00:14:11.233 --> 00:14:12.600
and whether inflation

00:14:12.600 --> 00:14:14.300
is unified

00:14:17.466 --> 00:14:18.533
If you look at it this way,

00:14:18.533 --> 00:14:19.166
then

00:14:19.166 --> 00:14:21.433
PPP GDP per capita with constant prices

00:14:21.433 --> 00:14:22.699
should be the best indicator, right?

00:14:22.700 --> 00:14:24.399
Well, not necessarily

00:14:24.399 --> 00:14:25.333
What is the best?

00:14:26.533 --> 00:14:28.166
You see, the official statistic

00:14:28.166 --> 00:14:29.233
after GDP figures for the year,

00:14:29.233 --> 00:14:30.566
all the unified conversions

00:14:30.566 --> 00:14:31.700
have to be estimated manually

00:14:31.700 --> 00:14:32.500
and calculated manually.

00:14:32.500 --> 00:14:34.233
Especially for countries like Iran,

00:14:34.233 --> 00:14:36.100
the official exchange rate and the actual exchange rate

00:14:36.100 --> 00:14:37.000
may differ greatly.

00:14:37.000 --> 00:14:38.399
The official inflation figures

00:14:38.399 --> 00:14:39.099
may not be accurate either.

00:14:39.100 --> 00:14:41.000
The outside world doesn't know the price level.

00:14:41.000 --> 00:14:42.233
So many adjustment factors

00:14:42.233 --> 00:14:44.366
need to be estimated by analyst at the

00:14:44.366 --> 00:14:45.833
World Bank and IMF thousands of miles away . 

00:14:45.833 --> 00:14:47.700
The more conversion steps you have,

00:14:47.700 --> 00:14:49.033
the larger the statistical error

00:14:49.033 --> 00:14:49.799
may be,

00:14:49.799 --> 00:14:51.166
especially for countries like Iran with

00:14:51.166 --> 00:14:52.599
insufficient data

00:14:52.600 --> 00:14:54.000
the accuracy is even lower.

00:14:54.000 --> 00:14:55.233
Leave alone World Bank

00:14:55.233 --> 00:14:55.899
even Universal Bank 

00:14:55.899 --> 00:14:56.433
wouldn't know

00:14:56.433 --> 00:14:58.033
how much is Iran's true inflation rate.

00:14:58.366 --> 00:15:00.333
This is essentially the art of statistics.

00:15:00.333 --> 00:15:01.733
The more perfect the indicator,

00:15:01.733 --> 00:15:03.833
the more human estimation and adjustment are needed,

00:15:03.833 --> 00:15:06.000
and the greater the calculation error becomes.

00:15:07.399 --> 00:15:09.899
This is somewhat similar to the uncertainty principle in quantum mechanics

00:15:09.899 --> 00:15:11.799
when the precision is high enough,

00:15:11.799 --> 00:15:14.666
position and momentum cannot be obtained simultaneously.

00:15:14.666 --> 00:15:16.133
However, quantum mechanics inherently

00:15:16.133 --> 00:15:17.933
possesses uncertainty in its physical properties,

00:15:17.933 --> 00:15:18.733
while GDP

00:15:18.733 --> 00:15:20.000
as a measurement,

00:15:20.000 --> 00:15:20.933
cannot be precisely measured.

00:15:20.933 --> 00:15:21.499
Therefore

00:15:21.500 --> 00:15:23.000
because of these statistical errors,

00:15:23.000 --> 00:15:24.599
when we look at economic data

00:15:24.600 --> 00:15:26.633
we usually choose a compromise.

00:15:26.633 --> 00:15:27.566
While there are

00:15:27.566 --> 00:15:29.433
ideal indicators of GDP that

00:15:29.433 --> 00:15:30.533
have everything adjusted,

00:15:30.533 --> 00:15:31.333
most of the time when

00:15:31.333 --> 00:15:32.700
we talk about a country's GDP, 

00:15:32.700 --> 00:15:34.833
we are referring to its current GDP in US dollars,

00:15:34.833 --> 00:15:35.966
which is the GDP of that year

00:15:35.966 --> 00:15:37.799
converted to US dollars using that year's exchange rate.

00:15:37.799 --> 00:15:38.433
Because this data

00:15:38.433 --> 00:15:40.599
doesn't actually have as many estimations and adjustments

00:15:40.600 --> 00:15:41.200
at the same time

00:15:41.200 --> 00:15:42.966
we can also make horizontal comparisons between different countries.

00:15:42.966 --> 00:15:43.299
Because

00:15:43.299 --> 00:15:44.733
of these many calculation methods

00:15:44.733 --> 00:15:46.433
you'll find a very interesting phenomenon

00:15:46.433 --> 00:15:47.233
except for the US,

00:15:47.233 --> 00:15:48.399
the GDP growth rate and annual GDP of

00:15:48.399 --> 00:15:49.199
other countries

00:15:49.200 --> 00:15:51.500
don't match up.

00:15:51.633 --> 00:15:52.233
What does this mean?

00:15:52.233 --> 00:15:53.566
For example, let's look at China's GDP

00:15:53.566 --> 00:15:55.600
The GDP in 2024 was $18.74 trillion, and

00:15:55.600 --> 00:15:57.399
in 2023 it was $18.27 trillion.

00:15:57.399 --> 00:15:58.033
Based on this calculation,

00:15:58.033 --> 00:16:00.533
the GDP growth rate in 2024 should be 2.6%.

00:16:00.533 --> 00:16:01.166
However,

00:16:01.166 --> 00:16:03.033
China's GDP growth rate in 2024

00:16:03.033 --> 00:16:03.966
was actually 5.0%.

00:16:05.433 --> 00:16:07.333
Similarly, for example, if we look at

00:16:07.366 --> 00:16:09.833
China's official GDP growth rate in 2021, it was 8.6%

00:16:09.833 --> 00:16:10.933
But if we calculate it based on 

00:16:10.933 --> 00:16:12.366
the annual GDP figures we just discussed,

00:16:12.366 --> 00:16:13.533
the growth rate would be as high as

00:16:13.533 --> 00:16:14.866
21.3%.

00:16:16.066 --> 00:16:17.366
Is there a mistake in the calculation?

00:16:17.366 --> 00:16:18.133
Actually, there isn't. 

00:16:18.133 --> 00:16:18.899
there's no mistake.

00:16:18.899 --> 00:16:20.833
Generally, when we talk about the annual GDP growth rate,

00:16:20.833 --> 00:16:21.899
we're referring to the local currency

00:16:21.899 --> 00:16:24.033
that is, the real GDP growth rate calculated after

00:16:24.033 --> 00:16:25.766
adjusting for inflation in RMB.

00:16:25.766 --> 00:16:27.966
But if we use the GDP figures from those two years

00:16:27.966 --> 00:16:28.966
to calculate the growth rate

00:16:28.966 --> 00:16:29.833
it's actually the

00:16:29.833 --> 00:16:31.733
growth rate after conversion to USD.

00:16:31.733 --> 00:16:33.566
It's too affected by exchange rate fluctuations

00:16:33.566 --> 00:16:35.233
making it less reasonable as a 

00:16:35.233 --> 00:16:36.033
short-term GDP indicator.

00:16:36.033 --> 00:16:37.199
But if we look at the long term,

00:16:37.200 --> 00:16:38.600
some people prefer to look at the USD.

00:16:38.600 --> 00:16:40.566
It's a matter of opinion.

00:16:41.566 --> 00:16:42.933
Anyway, after discussing so many

00:16:42.933 --> 00:16:44.399
different and varied GDP figures,

00:16:44.399 --> 00:16:44.866
I believe you've grasped the

00:16:44.866 --> 00:16:46.200
general idea

00:16:46.200 --> 00:16:47.066
that is GDP

00:16:47.066 --> 00:16:49.000
is not a single

00:16:49.000 --> 00:16:50.166
objective standard answer

00:16:50.166 --> 00:16:51.233
It is deceptive.

00:16:51.266 --> 00:16:52.899
It becomes misleading

00:16:52.899 --> 00:16:53.899
when it comes to horizontal

00:16:53.899 --> 00:16:55.033
or vertical comparisons.

00:16:55.033 --> 00:16:55.566
So

00:16:55.566 --> 00:16:56.933
whenever you see GDP

00:16:56.933 --> 00:16:58.733
you can always ask, 

00:16:58.733 --> 00:17:00.433
Which GDP are you referring to?

00:17:00.433 --> 00:17:01.899
This makes you seem very professional.

00:17:03.100 --> 00:17:05.333
Okay, we've talked about what GDP is,

00:17:05.333 --> 00:17:05.966
how to calculate it

00:17:05.966 --> 00:17:06.600
how to measure it,

00:17:06.600 --> 00:17:07.100
and how to compare it

00:17:07.100 --> 00:17:08.133
Seems like we've covered everything

00:17:08.133 --> 00:17:09.399
but there's still a fundamental question

00:17:09.399 --> 00:17:10.199
we haven't addressed

00:17:10.200 --> 00:17:12.299
why do people value GDP so much

00:17:12.299 --> 00:17:13.233
Why does it has to be GDP?

00:17:13.233 --> 00:17:14.566
Is it without problems?

00:17:15.833 --> 00:17:16.833
Of course, there are 

00:17:16.833 --> 00:17:17.700
many problems.

00:17:17.700 --> 00:17:19.000
What do we generally use GDP for?

00:17:19.000 --> 00:17:20.933
To measure a country's economic level

00:17:20.933 --> 00:17:22.199
or to give a very general

00:17:22.200 --> 00:17:24.366
idea of ​​its level of development.

00:17:24.366 --> 00:17:25.133
But economic level

00:17:25.133 --> 00:17:26.399
certainly involves more

00:17:26.399 --> 00:17:27.399
than just productivity.

00:17:27.399 --> 00:17:29.799
Let me give some common limitations of GDP

00:17:30.899 --> 00:17:32.599
For example, it doesn't measure income inequality

00:17:32.600 --> 00:17:34.399
it doesn't care about people's happiness or

00:17:34.399 --> 00:17:35.333
quality of life,

00:17:35.333 --> 00:17:37.433
it doesn't consider environmental damage

00:17:37.433 --> 00:17:38.966
and it doesn't consider sustainable development, etc.

00:17:38.966 --> 00:17:40.700
If you consider a country's economic development

00:17:40.700 --> 00:17:42.166
as a moving car,

00:17:42.166 --> 00:17:43.033
then GDP

00:17:43.033 --> 00:17:44.899
simply measures

00:17:44.899 --> 00:17:46.099
how fast it's going and

00:17:46.100 --> 00:17:47.766
where it's headed. 

00:17:47.766 --> 00:17:48.966
Whether the car itself is old or

00:17:48.966 --> 00:17:49.899
worn out,

00:17:49.899 --> 00:17:50.766
GDP doesn't care about any of that. 

00:17:50.766 --> 00:17:51.733
Frankly, these are all

00:17:51.733 --> 00:17:52.433
quite straightforward,

00:17:52.433 --> 00:17:53.166
so I won't elaborate.

00:17:53.166 --> 00:17:53.799
But even if

00:17:53.799 --> 00:17:55.333
we only want to measure economic productivity

00:17:55.333 --> 00:17:56.766
like how fast a car drives

00:17:56.766 --> 00:17:58.766
GDP actually has some problems.

00:17:58.766 --> 00:17:59.833
Let's talk about this.

00:18:00.533 --> 00:18:01.599
I wonder if anyone has heard of

00:18:01.600 --> 00:18:03.000
something called the "broken windows theory."

00:18:03.000 --> 00:18:04.333
In other words, a child

00:18:04.333 --> 00:18:05.166
breaks a window

00:18:05.166 --> 00:18:07.166
and pays someone to repair it,

00:18:07.166 --> 00:18:07.933
the whole process

00:18:07.933 --> 00:18:09.566
doesn't actually improve society

00:18:09.566 --> 00:18:11.766
and might even waste time or resources.

00:18:11.766 --> 00:18:13.833
However, the overall GDP is boosted

00:18:13.833 --> 00:18:14.799
because the window was repaired.

00:18:14.799 --> 00:18:15.633
We just mentioned that GDP

00:18:15.633 --> 00:18:17.433
doesn't measure the degree of environmental damage.

00:18:17.433 --> 00:18:18.633
In fact, not only does it not measure environmental damage, but

00:18:18.633 --> 00:18:19.966
if the environment is damaged

00:18:19.966 --> 00:18:21.000
or to put it more extremely,

00:18:21.000 --> 00:18:22.366
if there's a natural disaster

00:18:22.366 --> 00:18:23.266
followed by reconstruction,

00:18:23.266 --> 00:18:25.366
this can actually boost GDP in the short term.

00:18:25.366 --> 00:18:26.266
This clearly shows that

00:18:26.266 --> 00:18:27.799
the GDP indicator is malfunctioning.

00:18:27.799 --> 00:18:29.099
Furthermore,

00:18:29.100 --> 00:18:30.133
a purely false economic boom

00:18:30.133 --> 00:18:31.599
can also lead to inflated GDP.

00:18:31.600 --> 00:18:32.100
What does this mean?

00:18:32.100 --> 00:18:33.600
Let me give you an extreme example

00:18:33.600 --> 00:18:35.399
say I build a playground

00:18:35.399 --> 00:18:36.799
then I divided them into two groups, A and B.

00:18:36.799 --> 00:18:37.533
I said, "Okay,

00:18:37.533 --> 00:18:39.566
now group A will give group B a back massage

00:18:39.566 --> 00:18:41.333
Each person in group B will give group A $100 

00:18:41.333 --> 00:18:43.133
Regardless of whether group B needed the massage, everyone

00:18:43.133 --> 00:18:44.199
started massaging.

00:18:44.233 --> 00:18:45.566
After that, I said, "Okay, now group B will give

00:18:45.566 --> 00:18:47.733
group A a shoulder massage.

00:18:47.733 --> 00:18:49.100
Group A will then give group B $100 and

00:18:49.100 --> 00:18:49.899
start massaging.

00:18:49.899 --> 00:18:51.033
See how this goes on?

00:18:51.033 --> 00:18:51.999
In a single day, GDP

00:18:52.000 --> 00:18:53.133
might surge by tens of thousands.

00:18:53.133 --> 00:18:54.799
This is a very typical example of false prosperity.

00:18:54.799 --> 00:18:55.799
Sounds absurd, right?

00:18:55.799 --> 00:18:57.366
But it does happen in real life.

00:18:57.366 --> 00:18:59.000
Companies

00:18:59.000 --> 00:19:00.000
might collude to trade,

00:19:00.000 --> 00:19:00.799
offering each other

00:19:00.799 --> 00:19:01.533
"back massages" and

00:19:01.533 --> 00:19:02.366
"shoulder massages" to increase revenue.

00:19:02.366 --> 00:19:03.133
There's no profit

00:19:03.133 --> 00:19:04.233
but revenue goes up,

00:19:04.233 --> 00:19:06.033
and then the entire country's GDP goes up,

00:19:06.033 --> 00:19:08.033
This is a very typical example of false prosperity

00:19:08.033 --> 00:19:09.199
and GDP failure. 

00:19:10.333 --> 00:19:11.633
What I want to say is that

00:19:11.633 --> 00:19:13.966
even though we know GDP is imperfect

00:19:13.966 --> 00:19:16.166
but it is the most quantifiable

00:19:16.166 --> 00:19:17.599
and comparable indicator.

00:19:17.600 --> 00:19:19.566
Adding a bunch of adjustments like happiness indices,

00:19:19.566 --> 00:19:20.366
environmental indices, and

00:19:20.366 --> 00:19:21.500
income inequality,

00:19:21.500 --> 00:19:23.366
they won't actually make GDP more perfect

00:19:23.366 --> 00:19:25.200
On the contrary, it might make it easier to exploit loopholes,

00:19:25.200 --> 00:19:26.766
becoming more corrupt and unreliable.

00:19:27.500 --> 00:19:28.233
In statistics,

00:19:28.233 --> 00:19:29.200
if a concept

00:19:29.200 --> 00:19:31.366
cannot be measured stably and repeatedly,

00:19:31.366 --> 00:19:33.733
it has no practical significance at the policy level.

00:19:33.733 --> 00:19:35.366
For such large-scale statistical studies,

00:19:35.366 --> 00:19:37.700
reliability is often superior to validity.

00:19:39.200 --> 00:19:41.366
GDP is already

00:19:41.366 --> 00:19:42.700
the most reliable

00:19:42.700 --> 00:19:43.766
indicator of economic level that

00:19:43.766 --> 00:19:45.299
we can find

00:19:45.299 --> 00:19:47.133
that can be compared across time and regions

00:19:47.833 --> 00:19:49.133
In fact, think about other indicators

00:19:49.133 --> 00:19:51.799
even the most common one like inflation, CPI

00:19:51.799 --> 00:19:54.299
it measures changes in the prices of a basket of goods.

00:19:54.299 --> 00:19:55.599
But which basket of goods should be included?

00:19:55.600 --> 00:19:56.600
Should oil and housing

00:19:56.600 --> 00:19:57.933
be included

00:19:57.933 --> 00:19:59.466
It is a matter of debate among economists. 

00:19:59.466 --> 00:20:00.633
Take the unemployment rate, for example.

00:20:00.633 --> 00:20:02.333
It measures how many people are looking for work,

00:20:02.333 --> 00:20:03.733
and there's no universally accepted definition of 

00:20:03.733 --> 00:20:04.899
looking for work. 

00:20:04.899 --> 00:20:06.399
Therefore, unemployment rates across countries

00:20:06.399 --> 00:20:07.999
are practically impossible to compare directly

00:20:08.000 --> 00:20:09.366
GDP, on the other hand

00:20:09.366 --> 00:20:11.333
is clean, straightforward, and

00:20:11.333 --> 00:20:11.966
uncontroversial.

00:20:11.966 --> 00:20:12.766
This is why

00:20:12.766 --> 00:20:14.099
countries use GDP

00:20:14.100 --> 00:20:15.799
as the primary indicator of economic performance.

00:20:15.799 --> 00:20:17.899
We started by discussing GDP and the economy,

00:20:17.899 --> 00:20:19.833
but we've ended up talking about statistics.

00:20:19.833 --> 00:20:21.133
In short, you could say that

00:20:21.133 --> 00:20:22.599
a country's GDP

00:20:22.600 --> 00:20:24.366
is roughly equal to its economic level

00:20:24.500 --> 00:20:25.299
Now then

00:20:25.299 --> 00:20:26.833
shouldn't you ask another question

00:20:26.933 --> 00:20:28.966
Which GDP are you referring to?

